# API Conventions — 1BT WIKI REST API

## Versioning
- All routes must be prefixed with `/api/v1/`
- Router is mounted in `src/routes/index.ts` — never add versioning inside individual route files

```typescript
// src/routes/index.ts
app.use('/api/v1/articles', articlesRouter);
app.use('/api/v1/auth', authRouter);
app.use('/api/v1/users', usersRouter);
app.use('/api/v1/reviewer', reviewerRouter);
app.use('/api/v1/notifications', notificationsRouter);
app.use('/api/v1/tech-talks', techTalksRouter);
app.use('/api/v1/quiz-attempts', quizAttemptsRouter);
app.use('/api/v1/admin', adminRouter);
```

## HTTP Method Usage
| Intent | Method | Example |
|--------|--------|---------|
| Fetch list | GET | `GET /api/v1/articles` |
| Fetch single | GET | `GET /api/v1/articles/:id` |
| Create | POST | `POST /api/v1/articles` |
| Partial update | PATCH | `PATCH /api/v1/articles/:id` |
| Delete | DELETE | `DELETE /api/v1/articles/:id` |
| State transitions | POST | `POST /api/v1/articles/:id/submit` |
| Toggle/action | POST | `POST /api/v1/articles/:id/like` |

**Never use PUT** — always PATCH for updates (partial updates only).

## Route Naming Rules
- Plural nouns for resources: `/articles`, `/users`, `/tech-talks`
- kebab-case for multi-word resources: `/tech-talks`, `/quiz-attempts`
- Sub-resources use nesting (max 2 levels deep): `/articles/:id/comments`
- Actions (state transitions) as POST sub-routes: `/articles/:id/submit`, `/articles/:id/publish`

## Established 1BT WIKI Routes (do not rename these)

### Auth
```
POST   /api/v1/auth/signout
GET    /api/v1/auth/google/callback
```

### Articles
```
GET    /api/v1/articles                      ← list published (sort, search)
GET    /api/v1/articles/mine                 ← author's own articles (any status)
GET    /api/v1/articles/:id                  ← article detail
POST   /api/v1/articles                      ← create (Draft)
PATCH  /api/v1/articles/:id                  ← edit own draft
POST   /api/v1/articles/:id/submit           ← Draft → Pending
DELETE /api/v1/articles/:id                  ← author deletes Draft; Admin deletes any
```

### Comments & Likes
```
GET    /api/v1/articles/:id/comments         ← list comments
POST   /api/v1/articles/:id/comments         ← add comment
PATCH  /api/v1/comments/:id                  ← edit own comment
DELETE /api/v1/comments/:id                  ← delete own comment
POST   /api/v1/articles/:id/like             ← like (idempotent)
DELETE /api/v1/articles/:id/like             ← unlike
```

### Quiz
```
POST   /api/v1/articles/:id/quiz/generate    ← generate quiz from article (Claude API)
POST   /api/v1/quiz-attempts                 ← submit quiz answers
```

### Reviewer
```
GET    /api/v1/reviewer/articles/pending     ← list pending articles
PATCH  /api/v1/reviewer/articles/:id/approve ← Pending → Published
PATCH  /api/v1/reviewer/articles/:id/reject  ← Pending → Rejected + feedback
```

### User Management & Profile
```
GET    /api/v1/users/me                      ← own profile
PATCH  /api/v1/users/me                      ← update profile
GET    /api/v1/admin/users                   ← admin: list all users
PATCH  /api/v1/admin/users/:id/role          ← admin: change role
PATCH  /api/v1/admin/users/:id/status        ← admin: activate/deactivate
```

### Notifications
```
GET    /api/v1/notifications                 ← list notifications (auth user)
PATCH  /api/v1/notifications/:id/read        ← mark read
```

### Tech Talks
```
GET    /api/v1/tech-talks                    ← list published (sort, search)
GET    /api/v1/tech-talks/:id                ← detail
POST   /api/v1/tech-talks                    ← admin: create
PATCH  /api/v1/tech-talks/:id                ← admin: edit
POST   /api/v1/tech-talks/:id/publish        ← admin: publish
PATCH  /api/v1/tech-talks/:id/republish      ← admin: republish after edit
DELETE /api/v1/tech-talks/:id                ← admin: delete
```

### Admin Dashboard
```
GET    /api/v1/admin/dashboard               ← summary stats
GET    /api/v1/admin/users                   ← all users with roles
```

## Query Parameters (standardized)
```
?sort=created_at|title|event_date            ← sort field
?order=asc|desc                              ← sort direction (default: desc)
?search=keyword                              ← title search
?status=Draft|Pending|Published|Rejected     ← filter by status
?page=1&limit=20                             ← pagination
```

## Request Validation
- Use `express-validator` or Zod for all request bodies
- Validate in middleware before reaching the controller
- Return `400` with field-level errors on validation failure

```typescript
// src/middleware/validate.middleware.ts
export const validate = (schema: ZodSchema) => 
  (req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {
    const result = schema.safeParse(req.body);
    if (!result.success) {
      return res.status(400).json(errorResponse(result.error.message));
    }
    req.body = result.data;
    next();
  };
```

## HTTP Status Codes
| Situation | Code |
|-----------|------|
| Success (with data) | 200 |
| Created | 201 |
| No content | 204 |
| Bad request / validation | 400 |
| Unauthenticated | 401 |
| Forbidden (role) | 403 |
| Not found | 404 |
| Conflict (duplicate) | 409 |
| Server error | 500 |
